BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
PRODID:-//Chad Kuehn//Federal Holidays//EN
X-WR-CALNAME:Federal Holidays
X-WR-TIMEZONE:America/Chicago

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:newyears-2026@federal
SUMMARY:New Year's Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal public holiday marking the first day of the new year. Banks\, government offices\, and many businesses are closed.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260102
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mlkday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Martin Luther King Jr. Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday honoring the civil rights leader Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.\, celebrated on the third Monday of January. Federal offices and many businesses are closed.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260119
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260120
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:presidentsday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Presidents' Day
DESCRIPTION:Observed on the third Monday of February\, this federal holiday originally celebrated George Washington's birthday and now broadly honors all U.S. presidents. Also called Washington's Birthday officially.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260216
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260217
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:memorialday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Memorial Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday observed on the last Monday of May honoring the men and women who died while serving in the U.S. military. Marks the unofficial start of summer.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260525
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260526
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:juneteenth-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Juneteenth National Independence Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday commemorating the emancipation of enslaved African Americans\, marking the date in 1865 when Union soldiers brought news of freedom to Galveston\, Texas — two months after the Civil War ended.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260619
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260620
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:independenceday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Independence Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday celebrating the adoption of the Declaration of Independence on July 4\, 1776. Observed with fireworks\, parades\, and patriotic festivities across the nation.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260704
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260705
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:laborday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Labor Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday observed on the first Monday of September honoring the American labor movement and contributions of workers. Marks the unofficial end of summer.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260907
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260908
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:columbusday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Columbus Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday observed on the second Monday of October commemorating Christopher Columbus's arrival in the Americas in 1492. Also celebrated as Indigenous Peoples' Day in many states and cities.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261012
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261013
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:veteransday-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Veterans Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday on November 11 honoring all U.S. military veterans\, both living and deceased. Originally called Armistice Day\, marking the end of World War I in 1918.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261111
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261112
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:thanksgiving-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Thanksgiving Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday observed on the fourth Thursday of November giving thanks for the harvest and blessings of the past year. A traditional time for family gatherings\, feasting\, and reflection.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261126
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261127
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:christmas-2026@federal
SUMMARY:Christmas Day
DESCRIPTION:A federal holiday on December 25 celebrating the birth of Jesus Christ. Widely observed with gift-giving\, family gatherings\, and festive traditions across the nation.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261225
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261226
END:VEVENT

